# Keep the Docker build context clean and identical to a fresh CI checkout — never
# leak a developer's local install/build artifacts (which mask CI-only failures) or
# dev env files. Images install deps themselves; the encrypted infra/env/**/.env.staging
# is intentionally NOT ignored (the backend image bakes it).
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.log
.git
.github
# Dev-only env files (the runtime gets real values from dotenvx / the env_file).
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
apps/backend/.env
apps/backend/.env.local
apps/backend/.env.staging
apps/backend/.env.production
apps/backend/prisma/.env
